----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Model defines notification toggle operations with actor permissions and resource access control.
-- Summary 2: Safety assertions check authorization, resource access, and structural well-formedness.
-- Summary 3: Edge case assertions handle unsupported permissions and concurrent target access.
-- Assumption 1: Notification_Settings_Page is modeled as a Resource and Interface, but the spec uses it as a target in test predicates, which is valid only if it is a Resource; the model includes it as an Interface, not a Resource, so test predicates may be unsatisfiable.
-- Assumption 2: Actors Product_Management, User_Experience_Team, Development_Team have no explicit mayPerform permissions set, so assertions like ec_safe_1 may be vacuously true or false depending on instance.
-- Open issue 1: Notification_Settings_Page is declared as an Interface but used as a target (Resource) in test predicates; this type mismatch may cause unsatisfiability.
-- Open issue 2: Actors have no mayPerform permissions defined, so authorization checks may be vacuous; permissions should be assigned to actors to make the model meaningful.


